The paper proposes an automated deduction method based on tableaux and superdeduction, which is applicable to different first-order theories. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on formal proof generation, cs.LO is the most likely sub-category. The use of automated deduction methods also suggests cs.AI and cs.PL as possible sub-categories. The mention of the B formal method and the TPTP library suggests cs.SE as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of "superdeduction" suggests cs.LG as a possible sub-category, as this is a technique used in some machine learning algorithms.
